  "$schema": "https://aka.ms/codetour-schema",
  "title": "1: Setup",
  "nextTour": "2: Integrate Assistant0 with Auth0",
  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Introduction",
      "description": "## Introduction \n\nIn this lab, you will set up an NextJS+LangGraph AI assistant named Assistant0 that uses multiple tools to help you with everyday tasks. Tools add to your AI agent's capabilities by exptending its pretrained knowledge by connecting to first- or third-party APIs to perform actions on behalf of the authenticated user. \nFor example, a tool with Gmail and Google Calendar integration can help you speedily draft emails and schedule meetings.\n\nWe are going to add a tool to our AI assistant:\n\n1. **Gmail Integration**: Assistant0 will be able to search and draft emails on your behalf."
    },
    {
      "title": "Prerequisites",
      "description": "## Prerequisites\n\nIn addition to your Auth0 account, you will need a Google AI Studio account to generate a Gemini API key. Though you can use any AI model, we use Gemini for this lab since it has a free tier that does not require the input of a credit card.\n\n1. If you don't have one already, create a free account at https://ai.google.dev/aistudio. \n2. Sign into your Google AI Studio account.\n3. Select the **Get API key** button.\n4. Select the **+ Create API key** button.\n5. *If you have multiple existing projects in your account*, you will be asked to select a project and prompted to select an additional **Create API key in existing project** button.\n\n>Your Gemini API key is generated on the next page. Keep this open for the next step."
    },
    {
      "title": "Set GOOGLE_API_KEY",
      "file": "auth0-assistant0/.env.local",
      "description": "## Set GOOGLE_API_KEY\n\n1. From the Google Gemini window, select the key that was just generated (under the **Key** column to reveal its value.\n2. Select the **Copy** button to copy your API key.\n3. Paste this value on the line highlighted above to set the **GOOGLE_API_KEY** variable.\n4. You may now exit the Google AI Studio tab.\n",
      "line": 1,
      "selection": {
